# Docs / PRD maintenance

`docs/PRD.md` describes the **as-built** slide product. **`slides.md` and `pages/*.md` are authoritative for slide inventory**; update the PRD when the deck changes materially.

## When editing

- Keep goals, non-goals, and acceptance criteria aligned with a slides-only repo
- Do **not** move facilitator artifacts (agenda, timing, speaker notes, prep, Q&A banks) into “in repository” deliverables
- Brand tokens and assets (PRD §8) and link registry (PRD §6 / `data/links.ts`) must stay aligned with the deck and rules
- Prefer precise product language over copying slide prose verbatim

## Consistency checks

- In-repo vs out-of-repo lists must stay mutually exclusive
- PRD §4–§6 inventory must match wired `pages/` files and `slides.md` imports
- Learning outcomes (PRD §3) must remain achievable from slides alone (registry in `data/links.ts` is for maintainers until `06-resources.md` exists)
- Do not invent new brand systems or purple/AI aesthetics in brand requirements
